---
id: org.dxos.plugin.ibkr
name: IbkrPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

An Interactive Brokers plugin for `DXOS` Composer: a once-a-day background sync
captures a Flex Web Service report into a per-space feed (or the user imports a
Flex XML file manually from the toolbar), the assistant
answers portfolio, cash, and trade questions from the latest stored snapshot,
and `Instrument` objects provide navigable, deduplicated references to
tradable securities with static identity metadata plus research surfaces
(TradingView chart embed, SEC EDGAR fundamentals fetched at view time via operations).

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

## Architecture

```mdl
feat A-1: External access via operations

  req A-1.1:
    desc: |
      Components and surfaces never call external services (IBKR Flex, SEC
      EDGAR, or any other HTTP/API client) directly. All network I/O and
      service access flows through operations; operation handlers call
      `service:*` implementations.

  req A-1.2:
    when: a surface needs dynamic data from an external provider
    then: |
      it invokes the appropriate op via `OperationInvoker` (e.g.
      `useOperationInvoker` in React) and renders the operation output

  req A-1.3:
    desc: |
      Components may read static fields from their ECHO subject (`useObject`)
      and render presentation-only third-party embeds (TradingView chart
      widgets) that fetch their own market data client-side. The plugin does
      not implement parallel fetch paths in UI code.

  req A-1.4:
    desc: |
      `service:*` blocks are implementation details consumed only by operation
      handlers — never imported or invoked from `src/containers/` or
      `src/components/`.
```

## Types

The two persistent types are ECHO objects, identified by their DXN typename.
`Portfolio` is the navigable owner that appears in the navtree; `PortfolioReport`
is an append-only snapshot of the raw Flex XML. The `Position`, `Cash`, and
`Trade` structs are not stored — they are parsed from `PortfolioReport.xml` on
read and form the shape of the operation outputs.

```mdl
type Portfolio
  desc: |
    DXN typename: org.dxos.type.ibkr.Portfolio@0.1.0.
    Navigable owner of the Interactive Brokers reports feed. Appears in the
    navtree and opens the reports Article; its feed is hidden and carries the
    daily PortfolioReport snapshots. The feed is parented to the Portfolio so it
    cascade-deletes with it.
  fields:
    name?: string
    feed: Ref<Feed>             # hidden per-space feed of PortfolioReport snapshots
```

```mdl
type PortfolioReport
  desc: |
    DXN typename: org.dxos.type.ibkr.PortfolioReport@0.1.0.
    A persisted Flex report captured by the daily sync. Stores the raw Flex Web
    Service XML verbatim; read operations parse it so the rate-limited API is
    touched only by the once-a-day sync, never by chat.
  fields:
    xml: string                 # raw <FlexQueryResponse> document
    fetchedAt: string           # ISO timestamp the report was fetched from IBKR
```

```mdl
type Position
  desc: An open position parsed from a report's OpenPosition rows.
  fields:
    symbol: string
    quantity: number
    markPrice?: number
    costBasis?: number          # costBasisPrice, falling back to costBasisMoney
    positionValue?: number
    unrealizedPnl?: number      # fifoPnlUnrealized, falling back to unrealizedPnl
    currency?: string           # the instrument's own currency
```

```mdl
type Cash
  desc: An ending cash balance for a single currency (the BASE_SUMMARY rollup row is dropped).
  fields:
    currency: string
    endingCash: number
```

```mdl
type Trade
  desc: A single executed trade parsed from a report's Trade rows.
  fields:
    date: string                # tradeDate (YYYYMMDD), falling back to dateTime
    side: string                # BUY | SELL (buySell)
    quantity: number            # signed; negative for sells
    symbol: string
    price?: number              # tradePrice
    commission?: number         # ibCommission
    currency?: string
```

```mdl
type Lot
  desc: |
    A single tax lot (one acquisition). An OPEN lot — still held, parsed from a per-lot Open Positions
    row (identified by its openDateTime; levelOfDetail="LOT" when the query emits that column) — has no
    sold date and carries the current markPrice/value and unrealizedPnl.
    A CLOSED lot — a realized disposal, parsed from a <Lot> row in the Trades section — has a sold
    date plus proceeds and realizedPnl (the capital-gains data for tax reporting; long-vs-short term
    is derived from the holding period, indicative — IBKR is authoritative). Presence of sold
    discriminates the two.
  fields:
    symbol: string
    quantity: number
    acquired?: string           # openDateTime (acquisition)
    sold?: string               # tradeDate / dateTime (disposal); absent while open
    costBasis?: number          # costBasisMoney (open) / cost (closed)
    markPrice?: number          # open lots only
    value?: number              # positionValue; open lots only
    proceeds?: number           # closed lots only
    unrealizedPnl?: number      # fifoPnlUnrealized; open lots only
    realizedPnl?: number        # fifoPnlRealized; closed lots only
    currency?: string
```

```mdl
type AssetClass
  desc: Kind of tradable security represented by an Instrument.
  literals: stock | etf | mutual_fund | adr | reit | warrant | other
```

```mdl
type Instrument
  desc: |
    DXN typename: org.dxos.type.ibkr.Instrument@0.1.0.
    A first-class reference to a tradable security (stock, ETF, ADR, …).
    Holds static identity and descriptive metadata only — no prices,
    financial statements, insider rows, or other large or frequently-changing
    data. Dynamic market data (TradingView embed) and fundamentals (SEC EDGAR
    company facts) are fetched at view time and never persisted on the object.

    Deduplication uses `Obj.Meta.keys` (foreign keys). Each key is
    `{ source, id }`; an Instrument may carry several keys for the same
    security under different identifiers:

      - `isin` — ISIN (e.g. `US0378331005`)
      - `cusip` — CUSIP (e.g. `037833100`)
      - `ibkr.com` — IBKR contract id (`conid`) when known from Flex rows
      - `tradingview.com` — TradingView symbol (e.g. `NASDAQ:AAPL`)
      - `ticker/{exchange}` — exchange-qualified ticker (e.g. `ticker/NASDAQ`
        → `AAPL`; primary `symbol` + `exchange` fields remain the display
        default)

    Portfolio `Position.symbol` strings are not Instruments; materialization
    ops may create or resolve an Instrument from a position symbol.
  fields:
    name: string                 # display name, e.g. "Apple Inc."
    symbol: string               # primary ticker, e.g. "AAPL"
    exchange?: string             # listing exchange, e.g. "NASDAQ"
    assetClass?: AssetClass
    currency?: string             # trading currency, ISO 4217
    sector?: string
    industry?: string
    country?: string              # country of listing or domicile
    description?: string          # short business blurb; not filing bodies
```

## Components

```mdl
component PortfolioArticle
  desc: |
    Article view for a Portfolio: lists the stored daily PortfolioReport
    snapshots (newest first) from the Portfolio's backing feed. The toolbar
    carries the connect/sync action and a manual "import report XML" action
    (uploads a Flex XML file, appended via op:ImportPortfolioReport); clicking a
    report opens it in the complementary plank.
  props:
    subject: Portfolio
  state:
    reports: PortfolioReport[]   # snapshots from the Portfolio's feed, newest first
    selected?: PortfolioReport
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode          # hosts PortfolioSyncAction and PortfolioImportAction
  actions:
    selectReport(report: PortfolioReport)
  emits:
    onOpenReport(report: PortfolioReport)   # opens report in the companion plank
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [Connect / Sync]        │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ Report list             │
    │  ┌───────────────────┐  │
    │  │ 2026-06-25  · N/M  │  │  # date · positions/trades
    │  └───────────────────┘  │
    │  ┌───────────────────┐  │
    │  │ 2026-06-24  · N/M  │  │
    │  └───────────────────┘  │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component PortfolioSyncAction
  desc: |
    Toolbar action mirroring the Gmail mailbox connect/sync switch. The IBKR
    connection is detected space-wide by connectorId: when none exists it renders
    the connector's auth Surface (a "Connect Interactive Brokers" button); once
    connected it renders a Sync button that invokes SyncPortfolioReport for the
    Portfolio's space.
  props:
    subject: Portfolio
  state:
    connected: boolean           # a Connection with connectorId === ibkr exists in the space
    syncing: boolean
  actions:
    connect()                    # delegated to the connector's auth Surface
    sync()                       # invokes op:SyncPortfolioReport for subject's space
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ not connected:          │
    │   [Connect Interactive  │
    │    Brokers]             │
    │ connected:              │
    │   [⟳ Sync]              │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component PortfolioProperties
  desc: |
    Companion properties panel for a Portfolio: a single toggle that creates the
    daily sync trigger on first enable and enables/disables it thereafter. The
    user keeps a single trigger per space.
  props:
    subject: Portfolio
  state:
    syncEnabled: boolean         # reflects the daily-sync timer trigger's enabled flag
    pending: boolean
  actions:
    toggleDailySync()            # first enable creates the trigger; later toggles flip it
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ Daily sync       [ ●—— ] │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component PortfolioReportDetail
  desc: |
    Companion plank showing one PortfolioReport parsed into sections: aggregated
    open positions, trades, and cash balances, plus the per-lot breakdown (open
    tax lots) and realized closed lots when the query emits them. Parses the
    report's XML on render; purely a read view with no actions.
  props:
    subject: PortfolioReport
  state:
    positions: Position[]
    trades: Trade[]
    cash: Cash[]
    openLots: Lot[]             # per-lot breakdown; section shown only when non-empty
    closedLots: Lot[]           # realized disposals; section shown only when non-empty
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ Open Positions (N)                  │
    │ Symbol  Qty  Mark  Cost  Value  P&L │
    │ ─────────────────────────────────── │
    │ ACME     15  ...   ...   ...    +.. │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Open Lots (L)        # when present │
    │ Symbol Acquired   Qty Cost Value P&L│
    │ ─────────────────────────────────── │
    │ ACME   2024-01-15  10 ...  ...   +..│
    ├─────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Trades (M)                          │
    │ Date  Symbol  Side  Qty  Price      │
    │ ─────────────────────────────────── │
    │ 06-25 ACME   [SELL]  4   200        │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Realized Gains (K)   # when present │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ Cash                                │
    │ Currency   Ending Cash              │
    │ USD        1,000                    │
    └─────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component InstrumentArticle
  desc: |
    Article surface for an Instrument: static header (name, symbol, sector)
    from the ECHO object, a TradingView Advanced Chart embed (presentation
    widget only — no plugin HTTP from this component), and a fundamentals panel
    fed exclusively by op:GetInstrumentFundamentals (SEC EDGAR) via OperationInvoker.
    No fetched data is written back to the Instrument object.
  props:
    subject: Instrument
  state:
    tradingViewSymbol: string    # derived locally from Instrument fields/keys
    fundamentals?: FundamentalsSnapshot   # from op:GetInstrumentFundamentals only
    loading: boolean
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
  actions:
    refreshFundamentals()        # re-invokes op:GetInstrumentFundamentals
  layout: |
    ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ AAPL · Apple Inc.     NASDAQ · Technology       │
    ├────────────────────────────┬─────────────────────┤
    │                            │  SEC EDGAR facts    │
    │  TradingView chart         │  (revenue, EPS, …)  │
    │  (embed, client-side)      │                     │
    └────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component InstrumentCard
  desc: |
    Card surface (`AppSurface.CardContent`) for an Instrument: compact identity
    (symbol, name, exchange, assetClass) suitable for masonry, search results,
    and popovers. Optionally embeds the TradingView Mini Chart widget using
    `tradingViewSymbol` derived locally from the Instrument — no operations and
    no external service calls (fundamentals omitted to keep the card lightweight).
  props:
    subject: Instrument
  state:
    tradingViewSymbol: string    # derived locally from Instrument fields/keys
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ AAPL                    │
    │ Apple Inc.              │
    │ NASDAQ · stock          │
    │ [mini chart embed]      │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service FlexWebService
  desc: |
    Client for the Interactive Brokers Flex Web Service. A two-step flow:
    SendRequest yields a reference code, then GetStatement is polled until the
    report is generated. Calls route through the EDGE CORS proxy because Flex
    sends no CORS headers. Only the daily sync touches this service.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    fetchReportXml(token: string, queryId: string) → string   # raw <FlexQueryResponse>
    fetchReport(token: string, queryId: string) → FlexReport  # parsed positions/trades/cash
  errors:
    RateLimited: |
      Flex returned code 1018 or 1025. IBKR caps a token at 1 req/sec and 10/min;
      1025 locks the token after repeated failures. Stops immediately — retrying
      extends the lockout.
    SendRequestFailed: SendRequest returned a non-Success status
    NoReferenceCode: SendRequest succeeded but returned no reference code
    GetStatementFailed: GetStatement returned a non-retryable error code
    Timeout: report still generating after the maximum poll attempts
  effects: [http]
  note: |
    Pacing stays under IBKR's per-token cap: one SendRequest, a brief wait to
    space the first poll, then a poll every ~7s for at most 8 attempts (~50s).
    RETRYABLE codes (1001/1004-1009/1019/1021) keep polling; RATE_LIMIT codes
    (1018/1025) stop the flow; anything else fails fast.
```

```mdl
service SecEdgar
  desc: |
    Client for the SEC EDGAR public data API (`data.sec.gov`, `www.sec.gov`).
    No API key required; requests identify the app via a fair-access User-Agent.
    Invoked only from operation handlers (never from UI). Results are never stored
    on Instrument objects. Calls route through the EDGE CORS proxy.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    resolveCik(ticker: string) → string
    fetchCompanyFacts(cik: string) → FundamentalsSnapshot
  errors:
    TickerNotFound: unknown or non-US ticker
    FetchFailed: SEC request failed
  effects: [http]
  note: |
    Resolves tickers via `company_tickers.json`, then reads XBRL company facts.
    Parses headline filing metrics (revenue, net income, EPS, ROE, debt/equity).
    Respects SEC fair-access pacing (~10 requests/sec).
```

## Operations

Portfolio read operations parse stored XML and never call IBKR. Network I/O
reaches external services only through operation handlers (`SyncPortfolioReport`
→ `FlexWebService`; instrument research → `SecEdgar`). Components invoke
ops via `OperationInvoker`; they never import `service:*` clients.

```mdl
op SyncPortfolioReport
  desc: |
    Fetches a fresh Flex report from IBKR and appends it to the Portfolio feed as
    a PortfolioReport. Driven by the daily timer trigger, and also invokable
    on-demand from the toolbar or the assistant.
  input: {}
  output:
    fetchedAt: string
    positions: number           # count in the fetched report
    trades: number
    cash: number
  errors:
    MissingCredentials: connection is missing the Flex token or query id
    RateLimited: Flex rate-limit / lockout code returned (1018/1025)
    FetchFailed: SendRequest/GetStatement failed or timed out
  effects: [http, echo:read, echo:write]
  requires: [FlexWebService, CredentialsService, Database]
  note: |
    Resolves the credential (token from AccessToken.token, query id from
    AccessToken.account), fetches the raw XML, then finds-or-creates the
    per-space feed (keyed by IBKR_FEED_KIND) and appends one PortfolioReport.
```

```mdl
op ImportPortfolioReport
  desc: |
    Appends a manually supplied raw Flex report XML to the Portfolio feed as a
    PortfolioReport. Invoked from the toolbar's import action (file upload).
    Never calls IBKR, so it works without a connection — useful for backfilling
    reports downloaded from the Flex web UI.
  input:
    xml: string                 # raw <FlexQueryResponse> document
  output:
    fetchedAt: string
    positions: number           # count in the imported report
    trades: number
    cash: number
  errors:
    InvalidReport: the uploaded file is not a recognizable <FlexQueryResponse> document
  effects: [echo:read, echo:write]
  requires: [Database]
  note: |
    Validates the payload contains a <FlexQueryResponse> root before persisting,
    then finds-or-creates the per-space feed (keyed by IBKR_FEED_KIND) and
    appends one PortfolioReport stamped with the import time.
```

```mdl
op GetPortfolio
  desc: |
    Reads the open positions and cash balances from the most recent stored
    report. Touches no network — parses the latest PortfolioReport.xml.
  input: {}
  output:
    fetchedAt?: string          # absent if no sync has run yet
    positions: Position[]
    cash: Cash[]
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [Database]
  note: |
    Finds the per-space feed, takes the report with the greatest fetchedAt
    (ISO timestamps sort lexicographically), and parses it. Returns empty
    positions/cash when no report exists.
```

```mdl
op GetTrades
  desc: |
    Reads the trade history from the most recent stored report, limited to the
    last 7 days. Touches no network — parses the latest PortfolioReport.xml.
  input: {}
  output:
    fetchedAt?: string          # absent if no sync has run yet
    trades: Trade[]             # trades with date within the last 7 days
  effects: [echo:read]
  requires: [Database]
  note: |
    Same latest-report selection as GetPortfolio, then filters parsed trades to
    those on or after the cutoff (now − 7 days, as YYYYMMDD; IBKR trade dates
    sort lexicographically).
```

```mdl
type FundamentalsValuation
  desc: Valuation metrics (market data, price multiples).
  fields:
    marketCap?: number
    pe?: number            # price-to-earnings
    pb?: number            # price-to-book

type FundamentalsPerformance
  desc: Income-statement metrics from SEC EDGAR XBRL.
  fields:
    revenue?: number
    netIncome?: number
    eps?: number           # basic EPS

type FundamentalsRatios
  desc: Balance-sheet and profitability ratios.
  fields:
    roe?: number           # return on equity (decimal)
    debtToEquity?: number  # plain ratio, not a percent

type FundamentalsAdditional
  desc: Remaining us-gaap concepts from SEC EDGAR, keyed by XBRL concept name.
  fields:
    additionalFacts?: Record<string, number>

type FundamentalsSnapshot
  desc: |
    Transient output of op:GetInstrumentFundamentals. Parsed from SEC EDGAR
    XBRL company facts; not an ECHO type.
  fields:
    asOf?: string                  # SEC filing date
    valuation?: FundamentalsValuation
    performance?: FundamentalsPerformance
    ratios?: FundamentalsRatios
    additional?: FundamentalsAdditional
```

```mdl
op MaterializeInstrument
  desc: |
    Find-or-create an Instrument in the space, keyed by foreign id. Idempotent:
    returns the existing Instrument when `Obj.Meta.keys` already contains the
    given `{ source, id }`. On create, stamps the foreign key and seeds static
    fields from the input descriptor (name, symbol, exchange, assetClass).
    Does not fetch SEC EDGAR or IBKR — callers enrich via separate ops.
  input:
    key: ForeignKey              # e.g. { source: "ticker/NASDAQ", id: "AAPL" }
    name?: string
    symbol: string
    exchange?: string
    assetClass?: AssetClass
    extraKeys?: ForeignKey[]     # additional ids (isin, cusip, …) merged on create
  output:
    instrument: Ref<Instrument>
    created: boolean
  effects: [echo:read, echo:write]
  requires: [Database]
  note: |
    Primary entry for resolving portfolio position symbols into Instruments and
    for assistant-driven "open AAPL" flows. When `name` is omitted on create,
    a later op or manual edit may fill it in.
```

```mdl
op GetInstrumentFundamentals
  desc: |
    Fetches a compact fundamentals snapshot for an Instrument's primary
    `symbol` via service:SecEdgar. The sole entry point for SEC EDGAR data in
    the plugin — surfaces call this op; they never call the service directly.
    Returns transient filing-based data; never writes to the Instrument.
  input:
    instrument: Ref<Instrument>
  output: FundamentalsSnapshot
  errors:
    MissingSymbol: Instrument has no symbol
    TickerNotFound: ticker not found in SEC directory
    FetchFailed: SEC EDGAR request failed
  effects: [echo:read, http]
  requires: [SecEdgar, Database]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Connection

  req F-1.1:
    desc: |
      The user connects Interactive Brokers via the Flex Web Service by supplying
      a Flex token and a Flex query id through a Composer Connection.
  req F-1.2:
    when: the credential form is submitted
    then: |
      an AccessToken is created with the Flex token in token (the secret) and the
      Flex query id in account (non-secret); a Connection referencing it is created
  req F-1.3:
    desc: The connection is read-only — the plugin never places orders or mutates the IBKR account.
  req F-1.4:
    when: a connection already exists in the space
    then: component:PortfolioSyncAction shows the Sync button instead of Connect
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Daily Sync

  req F-2.1:
    when: the daily timer trigger fires (cron 0 6 * * *, 06:00 UTC)
    then: op:SyncPortfolioReport runs for the space

  req F-2.2:
    when: op:SyncPortfolioReport completes successfully
    then: |
      a PortfolioReport holding the raw Flex XML is appended to the per-space
      hidden feed; the report list in component:PortfolioArticle updates

  req F-2.3:
    desc: |
      Sync is the only path that calls IBKR. Read operations parse stored XML so
      the rate-limited API is touched at most once per day plus explicit manual
      refreshes.

  req F-2.4:
    when: the user toggles "Daily sync" on in component:PortfolioProperties for the first time
    then: the daily timer trigger is created (enabled); subsequent toggles enable/disable it

  req F-2.5:
    desc: |
      The local timer fires only while the app is open; gaps are covered by the
      manual Sync action and by the assistant invoking SyncPortfolioReport.
    tags: [limitation]

  req F-2.6:
    when: the daily timer trigger is created on first enable
    then: |
      the trigger and its serialized SyncPortfolioReport operation are parented
      to the owning Portfolio (Obj.setParent), so they cascade-delete with it
      and stay grouped under the visible object rather than at space root

  req F-2.7:
    when: the user uploads a Flex XML file via the toolbar's import action
    then: |
      op:ImportPortfolioReport validates and appends it to the per-space feed as
      a PortfolioReport without calling IBKR; the report list updates. Gaps in
      the daily timer (feat:F-2.5) can also be backfilled this way.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Rate Limiting

  req F-3.1:
    desc: |
      IBKR Flex is rate-limited (1 request/sec, 10/min). The client paces
      SendRequest and the GetStatement polls to stay under both caps.

  req F-3.2:
    when: Flex returns a rate-limit / lockout code (1018 or 1025)
    then: service:FlexWebService fails immediately with RateLimited; it never retries
    errors: [RateLimited]

  req F-3.3:
    when: Flex returns a retryable "still generating" code (e.g. 1019)
    then: the client waits and polls again, up to the attempt cap, then fails with Timeout

  req F-3.4:
    desc: |
      The assistant runs op:SyncPortfolioReport at most once per request and never
      in a loop; repeated attempts extend the token lockout.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Assistant Skill

  req F-4.1:
    desc: |
      The IBKR skill exposes op:GetPortfolio, op:GetTrades, and
      op:SyncPortfolioReport as tools the assistant binds to a conversation.

  req F-4.2:
    when: the user asks about positions or cash
    then: the assistant calls op:GetPortfolio and answers from the stored snapshot

  req F-4.3:
    when: the user asks about recent trades
    then: the assistant calls op:GetTrades and answers from the stored snapshot

  req F-4.4:
    when: the latest read result is empty (no sync yet) or the user asks to refresh
    then: the assistant may call op:SyncPortfolioReport once to populate or refresh

  req F-4.5:
    desc: |
      Each result includes fetchedAt; the assistant relays it so the user knows the
      data is an end-of-day snapshot, not a live quote stream. Amounts are reported
      in each instrument's own currency.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Report Browsing

  req F-5.1:
    when: component:PortfolioArticle is shown
    then: stored reports are listed newest first, each with its date and position/trade counts

  req F-5.2:
    when: the user selects a report
    then: |
      component:PortfolioReportDetail opens in the companion plank, parsing the
      report into open positions, trades, and cash sections

  req F-5.3:
    desc: Report rows and the detail view parse PortfolioReport.xml on read; no IBKR call is made.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Instrument Research

  req F-6.1:
    desc: |
      `Instrument` is the canonical ECHO type for tradable securities. Static
      fields only; foreign keys in `Obj.Meta.keys` register ticker, ISIN,
      CUSIP, IBKR conid, and TradingView symbol for deduplication.

  req F-6.2:
    when: component:InstrumentArticle is shown for an Instrument
    then: |
      the TradingView Advanced Chart embed loads client-side using the
      resolved TradingView symbol; a fundamentals panel loads via
      op:GetInstrumentFundamentals (SEC EDGAR)

  req F-6.3:
    when: an Instrument appears in a card context (masonry, search, popover)
    then: component:InstrumentCard renders static identity and may show the
    TradingView Mini Chart embed

  req F-6.4:
    when: op:MaterializeInstrument is invoked with a foreign key that already
    exists in the space
    then: the existing Instrument is returned and no duplicate is created

  req F-6.5:
    desc: |
      SEC EDGAR data stays ephemeral — op:GetInstrumentFundamentals fetches
      at view time; Instrument objects are not updated with filing payloads.
      TradingView embeds are presentation-only.

  req F-6.6:
    desc: |
      feat:A-1 applies to instrument research: component:InstrumentArticle
      invokes op:GetInstrumentFundamentals via OperationInvoker; no container
      imports service:SecEdgar or performs HTTP directly.

  req F-6.7:
    when: the user selects a position symbol in component:PortfolioReportDetail
    then: |
      the app may invoke op:MaterializeInstrument and open the resulting
      Instrument in an Article surface (future; not required for initial ship)
    tags: [future]
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Connect stores token and query id
  given: the user opens the Interactive Brokers connector form
  when: the user submits a Flex token and a Flex query id
  then:
    - an AccessToken is created with source interactivebrokers.com
    - AccessToken.token === the Flex token
    - AccessToken.account === the Flex query id
    - a Connection referencing the AccessToken exists in the space
```

```mdl
test T-2: Daily sync appends a report
  given: a connected Portfolio and a stubbed Flex response
  when: op:SyncPortfolioReport runs
  then:
    - a PortfolioReport is appended to the per-space feed
    - PortfolioReport.xml === the fetched <FlexQueryResponse>
    - the output counts match the parsed positions, trades, and cash
    - component:PortfolioArticle lists the new report at the top
```

```mdl
test T-3: Reads come from the latest snapshot only
  given: two stored reports with different fetchedAt timestamps
  when: op:GetPortfolio is invoked
  then:
    - positions and cash are parsed from the report with the greatest fetchedAt
    - no IBKR / FlexWebService call is made
    - fetchedAt in the result equals the latest report's fetchedAt
```

```mdl
test T-4: GetTrades is limited to the last 7 days
  given: a stored report containing trades older and newer than 7 days ago
  when: op:GetTrades is invoked
  then:
    - only trades on or after (now − 7 days) are returned
    - older trades are excluded
```

```mdl
test T-5: Reads return empty before any sync
  given: a Portfolio whose feed has no reports
  when: op:GetPortfolio is invoked
  then:
    - positions === []
    - cash === []
    - fetchedAt is absent
```

```mdl
test T-6: Rate-limit code stops the flow
  given: Flex SendRequest returns error code 1018
  when: service:FlexWebService.fetchReportXml runs
  then:
    - a RateLimited error is raised
    - no GetStatement poll is attempted
    - the error message advises waiting before retrying
```

```mdl
test T-7: Retryable code is polled then resolved
  given: the first GetStatement returns code 1019, the second returns the report
  when: service:FlexWebService.fetchReport runs
  then:
    - the client polls GetStatement twice
    - the parsed report is returned (positions, trades, cash)
    - no RateLimited error is raised
```

```mdl
test T-8: Sync without a connection fails clearly
  given: a space with no IBKR connection
  when: op:SyncPortfolioReport runs
  then:
    - a MissingCredentials error is raised
    - the message tells the user to reconnect under Settings → Connections
    - no PortfolioReport is appended
```

```mdl
test T-9: First daily-sync toggle creates the trigger
  given: component:PortfolioProperties for a Portfolio with no sync trigger
  when: the user toggles "Daily sync" on
  then:
    - a timer trigger on cron 0 6 * * * bound to SyncPortfolioReport is created, enabled
    - toggling off disables the same trigger without deleting it
    - exactly one sync trigger exists per space
```

```mdl
test T-10: Assistant answers from the snapshot
  given: a stored report and the IBKR skill bound to the conversation
  when: the user asks "what's my portfolio?"
  then:
    - the assistant calls op:GetPortfolio (not the network)
    - positions and cash are reported in each instrument's own currency
    - the answer relays fetchedAt as the as-of time
```

```mdl
test T-11: MaterializeInstrument is idempotent
  given: an Instrument with Meta.keys containing { source: "ticker/NASDAQ", id: "AAPL" }
  when: op:MaterializeInstrument runs with the same key and symbol AAPL
  then:
    - the existing Instrument is returned
    - created === false
    - no second Instrument exists in the space
    - a later materialization via a different alias folds the new key onto the same Instrument
  covered_by: operations.test.ts (idempotency + newly-learned-key fold)
```

```mdl
test T-12: InstrumentArticle loads chart and fundamentals
  given: an Instrument for AAPL with a tradingview.com foreign key NASDAQ:AAPL
  when: component:InstrumentArticle is rendered with a stubbed op:GetInstrumentFundamentals
  then:
    - the TradingView embed receives symbol NASDAQ:AAPL (derived locally)
    - op:GetInstrumentFundamentals is invoked via OperationInvoker, not service:SecEdgar from UI
    - the Instrument object is unchanged after render
  covered_by: |
    instrument.test.ts pins the local symbol derivation (resolveTradingViewSymbol); the
    InstrumentArticle story renders the surface. The "via OperationInvoker, not service" and
    "object unchanged" invariants are structural — the container imports no service:SecEdgar and
    only calls invokePromise (no writes). Asserted at render + logic level; no RTL harness exists
    for plugin components (behavior is covered by stories + test-storybook).
```

```mdl
test T-13: InstrumentCard shows static identity only
  given: an Instrument with symbol, name, exchange, and assetClass
  when: component:InstrumentCard is rendered
  then:
    - symbol, name, exchange, and assetClass are visible
    - no SEC EDGAR call is made
    - no fields are written to the Instrument
  covered_by: |
    InstrumentCard story renders the surface. "No SEC call / no writes" is structural — the card
    imports no service and invokes no operation (chart only, from static fields). Render-level
    coverage via test-storybook.
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap        # name[?]: TypeExpr  (# inline comment)
    literals?: UnionList     # a | b | c
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self              # feat blocks may contain feat blocks
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: dxos.spec/ext/test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap            # named input parameters
    output?: TypeExpr           # return type
    errors?: ErrorMap           # name: Prose  (when this error occurs)
    effects?: EffectList        # echo:read | echo:write | http | fs | ...
    requires?: ServiceList      # injected service dependencies
    note?: Prose                # implementation guidance (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap                 # name(params) → ReturnType
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
